[{"location":"","page":"Home","title":"Home","text":"CurrentModule = InterSpikeSpectra","category":"page"},{"location":"#InterSpikeSpectra","page":"Home","title":"InterSpikeSpectra","text":"","category":"section"},{"location":"","page":"Home","title":"Home","text":"Documentation for InterSpikeSpectra.","category":"page"},{"location":"","page":"Home","title":"Home","text":"","category":"page"},{"location":"","page":"Home","title":"Home","text":"Modules = [InterSpikeSpectra]","category":"page"},{"location":"#InterSpikeSpectra.create_single_basis_function-Tuple{Int64, Int64}","page":"Home","title":"InterSpikeSpectra.create_single_basis_function","text":"Create a spike-basis functions of length `N` and inter-spike-interval\n`period`. Due to time shifts, there are `period` different, linearly dependent\nbasis functions.\n\n\n\n\n\n","category":"method"},{"location":"#InterSpikeSpectra.generate_basis_functions-Tuple{Int64}","page":"Home","title":"InterSpikeSpectra.generate_basis_functions","text":"generate_basis_functions(N::Int) → basis\n\nGenerate a matrix `basis` with all possible `sum(1:N)` spike-basis functions.\nThese functions are not independent, since we account for time shifts. Thus,\n`basis` is a set of linear-dependent basis- functions.\n\n\n\n\n\n","category":"method"},{"location":"#InterSpikeSpectra.inter_spike_spectrum-Union{Tuple{Vector{T}}, Tuple{T}} where T","page":"Home","title":"InterSpikeSpectra.inter_spike_spectrum","text":"inter_spike_spectrum(s::Vector) → spectrum, ρ\n\nCompute a spike `spectrum` from the a signal `s`, using a LASSO optimization.\n`s` must be normalized to the unity interval `s ∈ [0 1]`. Second output `ρ`\nis the linear Pearson correlation coeffiecient between the true input signal\n`s` and the regenerated decomposed signal.\n\nKeyword arguments:\n`ρ_thres=0.99`: The agreement of the regenerated decomposed signal with the\n                true signal. This depends on the LASSO regularization parameter\n                `λ`. `λ` gets adjusted automatically with respect to `ρ_thres`.\n\n\n\n\n\n","category":"method"}]
